==English==

===Adjective===
# A problem that continues over an extended period of time, often associated with suffering ("long suffering").  
#''(medicine):'' 
##Prolonged or slow to heal. The opposite of [[acute]]. 
##A condition of extended duration, either continuous or marked by frequent recurrence. Sometimes implies a worsening condition (a condition which gets worse with each recurrence), though this definition is not [[inherent]] in the term.
#Inveterate or habitual. e.g. ''a chronic smoker''
#''(informal)'' 
##very bad, awful. e.g. ''that concert was chronic''
##extremely serious. e.g. ''they left him in a chronic condition''

===Noun===

#''(slang):'' marijuana, typically high quality

